1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,385
Every time you make a swap on a DEX, there's a good chance

2
00:00:04,485 --> 00:00:09,568
a bot saw your transaction in the mempool before it was included in

3
00:00:09,668 --> 00:00:15,291
a block, calculated that it could profit from your trade, inserted its own

4
00:00:15,391 --> 00:00:20,937
transaction before yours to move the price, let your trade execute at the

5
00:00:21,037 --> 00:00:26,506
worse price, then sold immediately after. You paid more than you had to,

6
00:00:26,606 --> 00:00:32,384
and the bot pocketed the difference. This is MEV — Maximal Extractable Value

7
00:00:32,484 --> 00:00:36,716
— and it extracts over $1 billion from users every year.

8
00:00:36,866 --> 00:00:41,649
Welcome to QuantiFire. MEV is money that validators or block

9
00:00:41,749 --> 00:00:48,160
producers can extract by reordering, inserting, or censoring transactions within

10
00:00:48,260 --> 00:00:54,101
a block. Originally called Miner Extractable Value in proof-of-work, it's

11
00:00:54,201 --> 00:00:59,717
now called Maximal Extractable Value. Understanding MEV tells you why

12
00:00:59,817 --> 00:01:04,274
your swaps get worse execution than you expect, and what

13
00:01:04,374 --> 00:01:05,902
you can do about it.

14
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:12,460
The mempool: Ethereum transactions don't go directly into blocks. They

15
00:01:12,560 --> 00:01:16,352
sit in the public mempool — a shared waiting room

16
00:01:16,452 --> 00:01:21,515
visible to everyone. Every transaction you submit shows the world

17
00:01:21,615 --> 00:01:27,075
what tokens you're swapping, what slippage you'll tolerate, your exact

18
00:01:27,175 --> 00:01:31,524
transaction parameters. MEV bots scan this in real time.

19
00:01:38,733 --> 00:01:44,764
Types of MEV: sandwich attacks are the most user-harmful — pure

20
00:01:44,864 --> 00:01:51,479
extraction from retail users. Arbitrage MEV is mostly beneficial — it

21
00:01:51,579 --> 00:02:00,042
restores price efficiency across DEXes. Liquidation MEV maintains protocol solvency. JIT

22
00:02:00,142 --> 00:02:06,855
— just-in-time liquidity — is mixed: users get slightly better prices,

23
00:02:06,955 --> 00:02:12,888
existing LPs get slightly less fees. MEV-Boost, used by 90% of

24
00:02:12,988 --> 00:02:20,576
Ethereum validators, redirects most MEV value to validators — democratizing MEV

25
00:02:20,676 --> 00:02:27,680
revenue. Defence: use private RPC endpoints like Flashbots Protect or MEV

26
00:02:27,780 --> 00:02:31,865
Blocker, and keep slippage tolerance tight.

